 Deuteronomy in the Temple Scroll and its Use in the Textual Criticism of Deuteronomy -- tPart II: Rewriting the Classical Literature of Ancient Israel -- t15 4Q364 and 365: A Preliminary Report -- t16 A Note on 4Q365, Fragment 23 and Nehemiah 10:33–36 -- t17 Three Fragments from Qumran Cave 4 and Their Relationship to the Temple Scroll -- t18 4QTemple? 4Q365a Revisited -- t19 The “Rewritten” Bible at Qumran: A Look at Three Texts -- t20 How Archaeology Affects the Study of Texts: Reflections on the Category “Rewritten Bible” at Qumran -- t21 What Constitutes a Scriptural Text? The History of Scholarship on Qumran Manuscript 4Q158 -- t22 The Excerpted Manuscripts from Qumran, with Special Attention to 4QReworked Pentateuch D and 4QReworked Pentateuch E -- t23 A Postscript on the Excerpted Texts -- tPart III: Final Thoughts -- t24 Textual Criticism of the Hebrew Bible in the Twenty-First Century: Theory and Praxis -- tCollected Bibliography -- tAncient Sources Index -- tModern Authors Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn the last several decades since the first publications of the biblical Dead Sea Scrolls, a revolution has occurred in the understanding of the history of the text of the Hebrew Bible during the Second Temple period. The present volume is a collection of articles documenting that revolution, written by Sidnie White Crawford over an almost thirty-year period beginning in 1990. As a member of the editorial team responsible for publishing the Qumran scrolls, the author was responsible for the critical editions of nine Deuteronomy scrolls and the four Reworked Pentateuch manuscripts; thus, her work played a critical role in the changing understanding of the textual history of the Pentateuch,especially the book of Deuteronomy and the Rewritten Bible texts. The author’s lifework is brought together here in an accessible format. While the majority of the articles are reprints, the volume will close with two major new pieces: a text-critical study of the Deuteronomic Paraphrase of the Temple Scroll and a comprehensive overview of the history of the text of the Pentateuch.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aBibel. 4aDeuteronomium. 4aQumran-Schriften. 4aTextkritik. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBible.  aDead Sea Scrolls.  aDeuteronomy.  atextual criticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104672770 cprintz978311046584640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311046742040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110467420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110467420/original  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099454-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022